Context:
The George Brown Digital Student ID can be accessed through the George Brown App. Students can request a physical ID card to be printed through the Photo Submission/Validation website. The student ID card grants access to college services and facilities, and it is necessary for academic activities. If lost or stolen, a replacement must be ordered. For Early Childhood Education students attending classes at Toronto Metropolitan University, a OneCard is required in addition to the George Brown College student ID.

Contact Information:
- Phone number: 416-415-2000 (TTY: 1-877-515-5559)
- Email address: ask.george@georgebrown.ca
- Social Media Hub: [Visit the Social Media Hub]

Important reminders:

- Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
